Regulus would not stay at Rome, while his fellow-captives were in the hands of the enemy: Cicero rather than stay in exile effected his return by violence and the aid of armed men. Cicero meets the objection by denying the use of force in effecting his return, which, he says, took place amid general popular enthusiasm: this gives him the opportunity of a detailed de- scription of the circumstances which accompanied his restora- tion.
